cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the study of traffic data and its effect on vehicular ad-hoc networks (VANETs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves statistical modeling and analysis, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Machine Learning). The study also involves the estimation of probability distributions, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
